make(T) - Static method in class common.Unique.Copy
Java doesn't allow this parameter to be declared: public Copy(U original) { super(original.copy()); } So we resort to a static factory method Unique.Copy.make, for when your type T is Copyable so you don't need to provide a Copier for it
